<LENGTH>
<P>
173 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTH FIRST! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The violent anti-slavery protests of John Brown before the Civil War, the 
women's rights protests at the turn of the century, the civil disobedience of 
segregation laws in the 1960s -- I think Earth First! protests can be added to 
that list. Their activities, while extreme, have at least made progress to halt 
the sellout of our resources to big business for an extra buck. 
</P>
<P>
When ecological legislation is unenforced or not effective, something else must 
be done. 
</P>
<P>
Our government is supposed to be of the people, not of the companies , and our 
natural resources are supposed to be protected for the people, not sold to 
private companies for exploitation. 
</P>
<P>
It's sad that the government's reaction is to hound these people instead of 
joining the fight to reclaim our planet. This is not eco-sabotage for the sake 
of publicity -- this is a fight for survival. I'll take the Monkeywrenchers and 
their tree spiking any day in preference to one more oil spill or one more pile 
of nuclear-power-plant waste. 
</P>
<P>
SHANNON DONNELLY 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
