<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTH FIRST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Change is always wrenching. To go from a Cold War economy to a peacetime 
economy is job wrenching, and to go from an economy of environmental 
destruction to one of harmony with nature is equally disturbing to those whose 
incomes depend on pollution, radiation or the irresponsible exploitation of our 
natural resources. 
</P>
<P>
Theoretically, most humans want to save our planet. The monkeywrenchers ask the 
telling question: "What are we willing to give up for it?" 
</P>
<P>
BURTON HENRY 
</P>
<P>
Temecula 
</P>
