<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAIN CORNER: THREE HOTEL CHAINS OFFER SUMMER CUTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several hotel chains are offering summer discounts. 
</P>
<P>
Inter-Continental Hotels has a "European Spectacular" campaign until Sept. 2 at 
37 hotels in 28 cities. The campaign includes a full American breakfast daily, 
an English-language newspaper daily and a packet with a city map and 
sightseeing information. All taxes and service charges are included in the 
basic room rate. 
</P>
<P>
Rates start at $89 a night, both single and double occupancy. No charge for a 
child 14 or under with a parent. Rates at the various hotels in the summer 
program represent as much as 60% off regular rates, according to 
Inter-Continental. 
</P>
<P>
Among the cities with participating hotels are Athens, Amsterdam, Belgrade, 
Berlin, Brussels, Budapest, Edinburgh, Frankfurt, Geneva, Helsinki, Lisbon, 
London, Madrid, Paris, Rome, Vienna, Athens, Bratislava, Brussels and Glasgow. 
</P>
<P>
Hilton International's "Summer Sale" program continues until Sept. 3 at 68 
properties around the world. Rates start at $59; tax and service charge is 
extra. 
</P>
<P>
At most hotels, a child can share the parents' room at no additional charge. 
One child free. 
</P>
<P>
SRS Hotels has a "Summer Celebration" program at 54 hotels in 14 countries 
until Aug. 31, with discounts of up to 53% off regular rates. Starting at $110 
on a double-occupancy basis ($75 for a single), rates include a buffet 
breakfast, plus tax and service charge. One child up to 12 can stay free with a 
parent, but the child's breakfast is extra. 
</P>
<P>
Among the cities with participating hotels are Berlin, Dusseldorf, Frankfurt, 
Hamburg, Munich and Nuremberg in Germany, plus Basel, Bergen, Innsbruck, 
Stockholm and The Hague. 
</P>
<P>
Eight Edwardian Hotels in London are participating in a "Midsummer Night's 
Dream" program that calls for up to 50% off room rates. Prices start at $99 
until Aug. 31, and include a full English breakfast, free accommodation for one 
child 14 or under, a gift voucher to Burberrys Department Store valued at about 
$18 and tax and service charges. 
</P>
<P>
The hotels are the Hampshire, Berkshire, Mountbatten, Kenilworth, Grafton, 
Vanderbilt, Skyway and Marlborough. 
</P>
<P>
Contact travel agents or Inter-Continental at (800) 327-0200; Hilton, (800) 
445-8667; SRS, (800) 223-5652, and Edwardian, (800) 447-7011. JACK ADLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061090-0030 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 231332 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 10, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part L; Page 34; Column 2; Travel Desk 
</P>
