<HEADLINE>
<P>
DICEY ICY TRUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the ton of ice in the June 3 News and Briefs, a 2,000-pound ice cube 
contains approximately 35 cubic feet. 
</P>
<P>
Doing some rough computations, I find that a one-ton ice cube is about three 
feet and three inches on a side. A meter. That is the "Fact." 
</P>
<P>
ALBERT P. PETRAITIS 
</P>
<P>
Escondido 
</P>
