<P>
Regarding: "To Brooklyn in Search of the Real Andrew Dice Clay" (by Patrick 
Goldstein, June 3): 
</P>
<P>
A very pretty portrait for your June 2 cover -- misogynistic bigot with 
fiancee. And such a sensitive young thing he turns out to be, only awful, 
really, when the eyes of the world are on him, and only then when he needs the 
money for his family. Heartwarming. 
</P>
