apologia for 2 Live Crew, Chuck D and N.W.A. Once you offer the 
poor-misunderstood-performer excuse for Silverstein, it seems that you're 
equally committed to shifting the focus of your rap lyric coverage from First 
Amendment rights to human interest. Or don't you bend over backwards to pander 
to hatred unless it's got the full force of a major studio publicity department 
behind it? 
</P>
