Geneva on Friday and was greeted enthusiastically by the assembly of the 
International Labor Organization. The black nationalist leader said later that 
he might have to cut back his grueling world tour after concerns were raised 
about his health. Mandela's visit to the United States is to begin June 20. 
Associated Press 
