<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLASH FROM THE PAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Effie Rogers was the first teacher at Duarte's elementary school, opened in 
1873 when 12 settlers petitioned the county for a school in their area. Rogers' 
salary was $65 per month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061090-0093 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 231512 </DOCID>
