<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William A. Moffett, director of libraries at Oberlin College in Ohio, has been 
appointed librarian of the Huntington Library, Art Collections and Botanical 
Gardens. 
</P>
<P>
He succeeds Daniel H. Woodward, who is stepping down to become a senior 
research associate. 
</P>
<P>
Moffett, 58, graduated from Davidson College and received master's and doctoral 
degrees from Duke University. At the Huntington, he will oversee a staff of 50 
and collections of more than 600,000 books, 750,000 prints, maps and 
photographs, and 2 million manuscripts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, William Moffett 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
