<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dale Greenhaw, 32, and Stanford Phipps, 36, of Pomona have completed a program 
to help ex-convicts acquire skills and find jobs. 
</P>
<P>
The men were honored at a graduation ceremony Wednesday night at the Pomona 
Church of Christ, which sponsors the Independent Living Training Center, a 
private, nonprofit organization founded by Don Golden, an ordained minister, 
and his wife, Linda. Currently, the center houses seven ex-convicts and also 
helps the homeless find housing and job training. 
</P>
<P>
Greenhaw, who was imprisoned 18 months for burglary, works as a food 
distributor and truck driver for the center. Phipps, imprisoned for two years 
for drunk driving, works at a Montgomery Ward warehouse in Chino as a quality 
control inspector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
