<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN'S DIVISION I DEBUT AT COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge has set its 1990-91 men's basketball schedule, one that 
includes 10 games against teams from the Big Sky Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge will begin its first season of competition as an NCAA Division I 
independent with three road games in four days. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors, 12-15 against a Division II schedule last season, will open at 
Colorado of the Big Eight Conference on Nov. 23. Northridge will finish its 
trip against two NCAA tournament teams -- Colorado State on Nov. 24 and New 
Mexico State on Nov. 26. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge will make its home debut Dec. 1 against Northern Arizona, which is 
among the seven Big Sky teams on the Matador schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Games at Cal State Long Beach (Dec. 12), at USC (Feb. 4) and at Cal (March 6) 
are other contests of note. 
</P>
<P>
A tentative schedule for next season that was included in Northridge's 1989-90 
basketball media guide included games against the likes of Dayton, Xavier and 
Wyoming. Those schools later removed Northridge from their schedules for a 
variety of reasons, Northridge Coach Pete Cassidy said. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
