<P>
THREE INFILTRATORS SEIZED NEAR ISRAEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Militiamen of the Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army captured three Palestinian 
guerrillas as they tried to infiltrate into northern Israel, the Israeli army 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The militia spotted the three-man squad moving towards the border about 2 miles 
north of the settlement of Misgav Am. In Lebanon, rival Christian forces 
skirmished with mortars in Christian East Beirut, raising fears that a fragile, 
23-day-old cease-fire brokered by the Vatican could soon collapse. In the 
southern port city of Tyre, the Syrian-backed Amal militia killed a Lebanese 
man accused of collaborating with Israel. 
</P>
