NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NEBRASKA; 
</P>
<P>
SOURCE OF TAINTED MEDICINE SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Food and Drug Administration investigator was trying to pinpoint the source 
of contamination in a solution that infected eight heart bypass patients, two 
of whom died. 
</P>
<P>
The patients at Bryan Memorial Hospital in Lincoln, Neb., are believed to have 
been infected by a contaminated batch of glutamate-aspartate, used in a 
solution to paralyze the heart during open-heart surgery. Two of the remaining 
six infected patients were in the intensive care unit. All six were listed in 
stable condition. The hospital also is asking the federal Centers for Disease 
Control in Atlanta to help determine how the solution became contaminated. 
</P>
