NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ILLINOIS; 
</P>
<P>
BLUES BROTHERS' SUITS SOLD FOR $12,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Blues Brothers' suits brought $12,000 and a red satin jacket with "John" 
embroidered on it fetched $1,400 at the John Belushi Memorial Auction in 
Chicago. "We're thrilled," said the comedian's widow, Judy Jacklin Belushi, who 
donated all the items in the sale, which raised more than $100,000 for a fund 
for aspiring actors founded in the comedian's name. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FUND RAISING; AUCTIONS; COMEDIANS; BELUSHI, JOHN; MEMORABILIA; CLOTHING 
</P>
