<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
<P>
* Plant a tree this summer to shade the hot spot in your garden next year. 
</P>
<P>
Choose from a good selection of container trees available now at nurseries. 
</P>
<P>
* One last planting of dahlia tubers will give you fall bloom as the plants you 
set out earlier are dying back. 
</P>
<P>
* When spraying plants for insects and diseases, don't forget the underside of 
the leaves. 
</P>
<P>
* It's not too late to plant tomatoes. Set them deeper in the ground than they 
were in the nursery container to prevent weak, leggy plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061090-0207 </DOCNO>
